<h3>Genome&nbsp;</h3>
<p>An organism's complete set of genetic instructions which are made up of DNA.</p>
<h3>Uses of genome sequencing.</h3>
<p>healthy baby - genetic diseases e.g. Mitochondrial DNA , shalabham in KR for newborn screening</p>
<p>Rare Disease - drug discovery&nbsp;</p>
<p>Evolution of human kind.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Community health - DNA strands responsible for demographic factors&nbsp;</p>
<p>COVID-19 = learn about mutations and predictive medicines (e.g. vaccine before disease outbreak)</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Personalised medicines</p>
<p>Scientifically assess traditional knowledge of personalised medicines , integrate traditional and modern medicine via evidence&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Wildlife conservation - could b used to conserve asiatic lion (canine distemper)</p>
<p>Wildlife crime detection (Tusk of elephant and tracing area, pangolin)</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
